1
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:06,700
We may think the position
of guru is one of master.

2
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:09,930
We say: the spiritual master,
prabhu, the guru.

3
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:13,100
[Guru: Master and Servant]

4
00:00:13,100 --> 00:00:16,090
He said, but really 
the position of the guru

5
00:00:16,090 --> 00:00:22,100
is to be the servant of the disciple, 
as much as the pūjārī

6
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:25,900
who’s preparing the fruit
to be offered to the deity.

7
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,150
What do they have to do? 
They take one fruit,

8
00:00:28,150 --> 00:00:31,900
a fruit comes 
into their possession.

9
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:37,300
They are the servant of the fruit,
not the master of the fruit.

10
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:41,900
The fruit has come to them, 
they think this fruit needs to be cleaned,

11
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:46,000
and then peeled of these things
and then fit.

12
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,300
Then it’ll be fit
to be offered to the deity.

13
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:56,300
So, the service of the guru is 
to cleanse the impurities of the disciple

14
00:00:56,300 --> 00:01:01,900
and then gradually through
proper instruction …

15
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:06,500
and infused spiritual conception,
those layers: karma and jñāna,

16
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:13,200
they are peeled away and then
the golden servitor is revealed,

17
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:20,600
who’s fit to enter the serving group
of the lotus feet of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa.

18
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:26,020
That’s the service
that is performed.

19
00:01:27,350 --> 00:01:29,000
And

20
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:35,500
Śrīla Saraswatī Ṭhākur—we’ve heard 
that he was saying, “Dāso ‘smi”.

21
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:40,000
First of all—calling his disciples
prabhu, which means ‘guru’.

22
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,510
Prabhu, we think,
“Oh, you call everyone ‘prabhu’ …”

23
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:44,300
No. 
It actually …

24
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:47,000
If you want to understand
what the word means—it means ‘guru’.

25
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,800
Only guru is called ‘prabhu’.

26
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:53,000
Why we are telling everyone
such-and-such ‘prabhu’?

27
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:59,800
Because Saraswatī Ṭhākur saw
his disciples as prabhu, as guru.

28
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:06,100
And he said—and if it ever, if ever
the time comes where I’m chastising them,

29
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:09,000
like: “I’m the guru and
listen to me for your own benefit!”,

30
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:13,700
he said, “If that type of mood comes”,
he said, “that is my pralāpa.”

31
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:18,600
Pralāpa means ‘delirium’. He said,
“Sometimes I become delirious

32
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:21,900
thinking I’m the master,
and you’re the servant.

33
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:25,000
But that’s a delirious condition

34
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,700
that should come infrequently.

35
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:34,740
Normally, I’m seeing myself
as your servant, dāso 'smi.”

36
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:41,800
And we might think,
“Oh, we are being told this—

37
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:46,300
these are stories 
that are being handed down.

38
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:49,070
Self–serving stories
that are being handed down.”

39
00:02:49,070 --> 00:02:53,100
Don’t think like that.
The fact is—it’s true.

40
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:56,700
You think how to readjust and
readjust, and readjust ourselves

41
00:02:56,700 --> 00:03:00,000
to the point, where we can come and
understand—these things are true;

42
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,400
they are not stories,
they are the truth.

43
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:06,600
The truth 
is being extended to us.

44
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:12,100
And it’s only being
limited by our disbelief,

45
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:16,200
or causeless
unwillingness to believe.

46
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:18,400
That expression sometimes 
Prabhupāda used to—

47
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:21,400
‘a causeless unwillingness’.

48
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,500
Where does it come from?

49
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:29,100
Guru Mahārāj called ‘the anti-Kṛṣṇa 
tendencies we have acquired’.

50
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:32,200
Where do they come from?
It’s so unfortunate.

51
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,430
But our good fortune,
bhāgyavān jīva,

52
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:38,800
is to come in connection 
with the lotus feet of guru and Vaiṣṇava.

53
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:41,800
That’s all good fortune.
Guru Mahārāja said

54
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:45,600
then in the end of that
‘Śrī Guru’ preface he said,

55
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:51,000
“When the gentle hand of Śrī Guru 
wipes away all the tears

56
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,800
of the suffering souls 
in this world”—

57
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:59,800
that is why Kṛṣṇa is manifesting 
Himself to us as guru.

